article.description: C.J. Bobbitt scored 17 points while hauling in 12 rebounds, and Joe Rosga hit the go-ahead bucket with 12 seconds remaining Saturday night to lift Denver past Weber State 57-55.
article.headline: Denver edges Weber State 57-55
article.story: OGDEN, Utah -- C.J. Bobbitt scored 17 points while hauling in 12 rebounds, and Joe Rosga hit the go-ahead bucket with 12 seconds remaining Saturday night to lift Denver past Weber State 57-55. In a back-and-forth second half, Denver (3-4) tied the game at 55-all on Bobbitt's jumper with 2:12 left, then both teams went cold over the next two minutes before Rosga made the winning basket. Weber State's Jeremy Senglin missed a 3-pointer at the other end with eight seconds left and Denver got the rebound to seal the win. Bobbitt shot 8 for 10 from the field and his double-double was a career first. Daniel Amigo contributed 12 points, Jake Pemberton added 10 and Rosga finished with eight for the Pioneers. Weber State got 15 points from Senglin. Kyndahl Hill added 14 points and 12 rebounds.
